               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18451027-name-1232" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18451027-name-1232" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18451027-name-1232" type="surname" value="ROLFE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18451027-name-1232" type="given" value="ANN ELIZABETH"></interp>ANN ELIZABETH ROLFE</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a servant—I live in Duke's-court, Union-street, Borough—on the 4th of Oct., at half-past eleven o'clock at night, I was standing on the pavement, where there were some people looking at a man—the officer told me something—I put my hand into my pocket and missed a sovereign, a shilling, and a sixpence, which I had had safe not a minute before, wrapped in a small piece of paper—I cannot swear that I saw the prisoner.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18451027-name-1233" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18451027-name-1233" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18451027-name-1233" type="surname" value="BRANSFORD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18451027-name-1233" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>ROBERT BRANSFORD</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable M</hi> 101.) I was on duty in Union-street, in the Borough—I saw the prisoner lift the prosecutrix's dress about a foot from the ground—I saw his hand in her pocket-hole—I watched him—one of his companions told him of it, and he left her—I went and spoke to her, and he disappeared—I took him about an hour afterwards.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> I was going home that Saturday night, about eleven o'clock; I passed by a crowd; I was going home again, and the officer came and said I had picked a lady's pocket.</p>
